s=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526220\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 10, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bsu1665702657892.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bsu1665702657892.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bsu1665702657892.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bsu1665702657892\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Uniface Mappings to Installable Character Sets\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__uniface_mappings_to_installable_character_sets_93718\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">During Uniface installation, it is possible to choose a character set that is appropriate for one or more languages. Thus Western European is appropriate for English, German, French and so on, and Cyrillic is appropriate for Slavic languages such as Russian.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__p_d28673e1_d28674e1_d28675e1\">The character set name is generic, for example Western European, Cyrillic, or Simplified Chinese, but the actual character set installed is specific to the platform. Different platforms use different character set standards. Uniface uses one name to represent the different character sets that represent the same characters. For example, CP1251 and ISO 8859-5 are character sets in different platforms to represent Cyrillic characters. Uniface uses <code class=\"ph codeph\">Cyrillic</code> to represent all of them. The generic character set is also referred to as a <var class=\"keyword varname\">meta variant</var>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__p_d28676e1_d28677e1_d28678e1\">Each meta variant is mapped to several installable character sets, as listed in the following table, in which the column headings mean the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__li_d14603e1_d14604e1_d14605e1\">Type—Type of character sets. For more information,\n            see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jvf1665702657960.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jvf1665702657960.html\" title=\"The installable character sets can be either single-byte or double-byte. Single-byte character sets can be divided into left-to-right and right-to-left.\">Types of Character Sets</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__li_d14606e1_d14607e1_d14608e1\">Meta Variant—Generic character set name used in\n            Uniface, for example, in the Character set selection screen during Uniface installation\n            and in translation tables. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__li_d14609e1_d14610e1_d14611e1\">Microsoft Windows—Windows code page or character set corresponding to the meta variant. When installing Uniface on Windows, the Character set selection screen lists only the character sets supported by Windows (the first 11 character sets in the table).\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__li_d14612e1_d14613e1_d14614e1\">Unix—Unix character set corresponding to the meta variant.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__li_d14615e1_d14616e1_d14617e1\">iSeries—Code Character Set Identifier (CCSID) corresponding to the meta variant. The iSeries systems are EBCDIC-based platforms. They are used only to run Uniface servers. Different character sets are used in different systems or different version of systems.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"4\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Installable Character Sets</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__1\">\n Type\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__2\">\n Meta Variant\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__3\">\n Microsoft Windows\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__4\">\n Unix\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"4\">\n Single-byte (LTR)\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__2\">\n Western European (or English)\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__3\">\n CP1252\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__4\">\n ISO 8859-1\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__2\">\n Central European\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__3\">\n CP1250\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__4\">\n ISO 8859-2\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__2\">\n Cyrillic\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__3\">\n CP1251\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__4\">\n ISO 8859-5\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__2\">\n Greek\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__3\">\n CP1253\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__4\">\n ISO 8859-7\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"2\">\n Single-byte (LTR+RTL)\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__2\">\n Arabic\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">CP1256</p>\n<p class=\"p\">CP708(7-bit)</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__4\">\n<p class=\"p\">ISO 8859-6</p>\n<p class=\"p\">ISO 9036(7-bit)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__2\">\n Hebrew\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__3\">\n CP1255\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__4\">\n<p class=\"p\">ISO 8859-8</p>\n<p class=\"p\">ISO 8859-8-1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"4\">\n Double-byte\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__2\">\n Simplified Chinese\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__3\">\n CP936\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__4\">\n GB2312-80\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__2\">\n Korean\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__3\">\n CP949\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__4\">\n KSC5601-1992\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__2\">\n Japanese\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__3\">\n CP932(Shift-JIS)\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__4\">\n ISO 2022-JP(EUC-JP)\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__2\">\n Traditional Chinese\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__3\">\n CP932 (BIG5)\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bsu1665702657892__table_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1__entry__4\">\n BIG5\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__topic_d19152e1_d19153e1_d19154e1_d19155e1_d19156e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d784707e278\">\n                  \n More Information\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__p_d28682e1_d28683e1_d28684e1\">For more information on platform-specific character sets for, see the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__li_d14618e1_d14619e1_d14620e1\">\n<cite class=\"cite\">Developing International Software, second Edition, Microsoft programming series, Microsoft Press, 2002</cite>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__li_d14621e1_d14622e1_d14623e1\">\n<cite class=\"cite\">ISO Standard</cite>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bsu1665702657892__li_d14624e1_d14625e1_d14626e1\">\n<cite class=\"cite\">IBM's iSeries Information Center</cite>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lkd1665702657821.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Installable Character Sets</a><p>Character sets that conform to one of several characters encoding systems can be installed into Uniface applications.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526220\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526220\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface Mappings to Installable Character Sets Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 10, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface Mappings to Installable Character Sets During Uniface installation, it is possible to choose a character set that is appropriate for one or more languages. Thus Western European is appropriate for English, German, French and so on, and Cyrillic is appropriate for Slavic languages such as Russian. The character set name is generic, for example Western European, Cyrillic, or Simplified Chinese, but the actual character set installed is specific to the platform. Different platforms use different character set standards. Uniface uses one name to represent the different character sets that represent the same characters. For example, CP1251 and ISO 8859-5 are character sets in different platforms to represent Cyrillic characters. Uniface uses Cyrillic to represent all of them. The generic character set is also referred to as a meta variant . Each meta variant is mapped to several installable character sets, as listed in the following table, in which the column headings mean the following: Type—Type of character sets. For more information, see Types of Character Sets . Meta Variant—Generic character set name used in Uniface, for example, in the Character set selection screen during Uniface installation and in translation tables. Microsoft Windows—Windows code page or character set corresponding to the meta variant. When installing Uniface on Windows, the Character set selection screen lists only the character sets supported by Windows (the first 11 character sets in the table). Unix—Unix character set corresponding to the meta variant. iSeries—Code Character Set Identifier (CCSID) corresponding to the meta variant. The iSeries systems are EBCDIC-based platforms. They are used only to run Uniface servers. Different character sets are used in different systems or different version of systems. Table 1. Installable Character Sets Type Meta Variant Microsoft Windows Unix Single-byte (LTR) Western European (or English) CP1252 ISO 8859-1 Central European CP1250 ISO 8859-2 Cyrillic CP1251 ISO 8859-5 Greek CP1253 ISO 8859-7 Single-byte (LTR+RTL) Arabic CP1256 CP708(7-bit) ISO 8859-6 ISO 9036(7-bit) Hebrew CP1255 ISO 8859-8 ISO 8859-8-1 Double-byte Simplified Chinese CP936 GB2312-80 Korean CP949 KSC5601-1992 Japanese CP932(Shift-JIS) ISO 2022-JP(EUC-JP) Traditional Chinese CP932 (BIG5) BIG5 More Information For more information on platform-specific character sets for, see the following: Developing International Software, second Edition, Microsoft programming series, Microsoft Press, 2002 ISO Standard IBM's iSeries Information Center Related Links Installable Character Sets Character sets that conform to one of several characters encoding systems can be installed into Uniface applications. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}